Now I'll calculate each ratio:

2. Quick Ratio = Quick Assets / Current Liabilities
   = $3,006,942.43 / $5,637,910.70
   = 0.53

3. Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Debt / Total Assets
   = $5,637,910.70 / $21,737,442.99
   = 0.26

4. Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Debt / Total Equity
   = $5,637,910.70 / $16,099,532.29
   = 0.35

5. Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Debt
   = -$1,919,526.63 / $5,637,910.70
   = -0.34
